 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-jrhe","title":"P6.7: Accessibility Testing (WCAG 2.1 AA)","description":"# P6.7: Accessibility Testing (WCAG 2.1 AA)

## Overview
Ensure the web viewer is accessible to users with disabilities, following WCAG 2.1 AA guidelines. Referenced in P6.14 Master E2E Test Suite but needs dedicated implementation.

## Why Accessibility Matters
- Legal compliance (ADA, Section 508, EU directives)
- Inclusive design benefits all users
- Screen reader users should be able to search and browse archives
- Keyboard-only navigation must be fully functional

## WCAG 2.1 AA Checklist

### Perceivable
- [ ] All images have alt text (or are decorative with empty alt)
- [ ] Color is not the only visual indicator
- [ ] Contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for normal text, ≥ 3:1 for large text
- [ ] Text can be resized up to 200% without loss of functionality
- [ ] Page content reflows at 320px width without horizontal scrolling

### Operable
- [ ] All functionality available via keyboard
- [ ] No keyboard traps (can tab in and out of all elements)
- [ ] Focus visible on all interactive elements
- [ ] Skip navigation link provided
- [ ] Focus order logical and sequential
- [ ] No content flashes more than 3 times per second

### Understandable
- [ ] Page language declared in HTML
- [ ] Form fields have visible labels
- [ ] Error messages identify the error and suggest correction
- [ ] Consistent navigation structure across pages

### Robust
- [ ] Valid HTML (passes W3C validator)
- [ ] ARIA attributes used correctly
- [ ] Name, role, value exposed for custom widgets

## Implementation

### Semantic HTML
